  <compounddef id="SOCKBINWRITE" kind="page">
    <compoundname>SOCKBINWRITE</compoundname>
    <title>SOCKBINWRITE Statement</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">SOCKBINWRITE(integer-socket,<sp/>integer-buffer,<sp/>integer-length)</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Writes <bold>binary data</bold> from memory to a <bold>connected socket</bold>.</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>integer-socket</computeroutput> — socket file descriptor (e.g. from <ref refid="CONNECT" kindref="compound">CONNECT</ref> or <ref refid="SOCKACCEPT" kindref="compound">SOCKACCEPT</ref>).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>integer-buffer</computeroutput> — memory handle/pointer returned by <ref refid="MEMALLOC" kindref="compound">MEMALLOC</ref>.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>integer-length</computeroutput> — number of bytes to write.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<sect3 id="SOCKBINWRITE_1autotoc_md1020">
<title>Examples</title>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">size<sp/>=<sp/>FILESIZE(file$)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">buf<sp/><sp/>=<sp/>MEMALLOC(size)</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">BINREAD<sp/>fh,<sp/>buf,<sp/>size</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">SOCKWRITE<sp/>client,<sp/>&quot;Content-Length:<sp/>&quot;;<sp/>size;<sp/>CHR$(13);<sp/>CHR$(10);<sp/>CHR$(13);<sp/>CHR$(10);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">SOCKBINWRITE<sp/>client,<sp/>buf,<sp/>size</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">SOCKFLUSH<sp/>client</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">MEMRELEASE<sp/>buf</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
</sect3>
<sect3 id="SOCKBINWRITE_1autotoc_md1022">
<title>Notes</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Intended for sending file contents or other raw buffers.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Socket must be connected; use <ref refid="SOCKSTATUS" kindref="compound">SOCKSTATUS</ref> to check.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>May write less than requested if the peer closes; handle errors accordingly.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
